{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Aside from keeping the rain out and producing some usable space,"},{"time":7000,"text":"architecture is nothing but a special-effects machine"},{"time":11000,"text":"that delights and disturbs the senses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":14000,"text":"Our work is across media. The work comes in all shapes and sizes."},{"time":19000,"text":"It's small and large. This is an ashtray, a water glass."},{"time":23000,"text":"From urban planning and master planning"},{"time":26000,"text":"to theater and all sorts of stuff."},{"time":30000,"text":"The thing that all the work has in common"},{"time":32000,"text":"is that it challenges the assumptions about conventions of space."},{"time":37000,"text":"And these are everyday conventions,"},{"time":39000,"text":"conventions that are so obvious that we are blinded by their familiarity."},{"time":44000,"text":"And I've assembled a sampling of work"},{"time":48000,"text":"that all share a kind of productive nihilism"},{"time":52000,"text":"that's used in the service of creating a particular special effect."},{"time":56000,"text":"And that is something like nothing, or something next to nothing."},{"time":62000,"text":"It's done through a form of subtraction or obstruction or interference"},{"time":67000,"text":"in a world that we naturally sleepwalk through."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71000,"text":"This is an image that won us a competition"},{"time":74000,"text":"for an exhibition pavilion for the Swiss Expo 2002"},{"time":78000,"text":"on Lake Neuchatel, near Geneva."},{"time":80000,"text":"And we wanted to use the water not only as a context,"},{"time":83000,"text":"but as a primary building material."},{"time":85000,"text":"We wanted to make an architecture of atmosphere."},{"time":88000,"text":"So, no walls, no roof, no purpose --"},{"time":91000,"text":"just a mass of atomized water, a big cloud."},{"time":94000,"text":"And this proposal was a reaction to the over-saturation"},{"time":97000,"text":"of emergent technologies in recent national and world expositions,"},{"time":102000,"text":"which feeds, or has been feeding, our insatiable appetite"},{"time":107000,"text":"for visual stimulation with an ever greater digital virtuosity."},{"time":113000,"text":"High definition, in our opinion, has become the new orthodoxy."},{"time":118000,"text":"And we ask the question, can we use technology, high technology,"},{"time":122000,"text":"to make an expo pavilion that's decidedly low definition,"},{"time":128000,"text":"that also challenges the conventions of space and skin,"},{"time":131000,"text":"and rethinks our dependence on vision?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":133000,"text":"So this is how we sought to do it."},{"time":136000,"text":"Water's pumped from the lake and is filtered"},{"time":138000,"text":"and shot as a fine mist through an array of high-pressure fog nozzles,"},{"time":143000,"text":"35,000 of them. And a weather station is on the structure."},{"time":147000,"text":"It reads the shifting conditions of temperature, humidity,"},{"time":150000,"text":"wind direction, wind speed, dew point,"},{"time":153000,"text":"and it processes this data in a central computer"},{"time":156000,"text":"that calibrates the degree of water pressure"},{"time":159000,"text":"and distribution of water throughout."},{"time":161000,"text":"And it's a responsive system that's trained on actual weather."},{"time":166000,"text":"So, this is just in construction, and there's a tensegrity structure."},{"time":170000,"text":"It's about 300 feet wide, the size of a football field,"},{"time":173000,"text":"and it sits on just four very delicate columns."},{"time":177000,"text":"These are the fog nozzles, the interface,"},{"time":180000,"text":"and basically the system is kind of reading the real weather,"},{"time":184000,"text":"and producing kind of semi-artificial and real weather."},{"time":188000,"text":"So, we're very interested in creating weather. I don't know why."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192000,"text":"Now, here we go, one side, the outside"},{"time":195000,"text":"and then from the inside of the space"},{"time":197000,"text":"you can see what the quality of the space was."},{"time":199000,"text":"Unlike entering any normal space,"},{"time":202000,"text":"entering Blur is like stepping into a habitable medium."},{"time":206000,"text":"It's formless, featureless, depthless, scaleless, massless,"},{"time":211000,"text":"purposeless and dimensionless."},{"time":213000,"text":"All references are erased,"},{"time":216000,"text":"leaving only an optical whiteout and white noise of the pulsing nozzles."},{"time":222000,"text":"So, this is an exhibition pavilion"},{"time":225000,"text":"where there is absolutely nothing to see and nothing to do."},{"time":229000,"text":"And we pride ourselves -- it's a spectacular anti-spectacle"},{"time":235000,"text":"in which all the conventions of spectacle are turned on their head."},{"time":239000,"text":"So, the audience is dispersed,"},{"time":241000,"text":"focused attention and dramatic build-up and climax"},{"time":244000,"text":"are all replaced by a kind of attenuated attention"},{"time":247000,"text":"that's sustained by a sense of apprehension caused by the fog."},{"time":251000,"text":"And this is very much like how the Victorian novel used fog in this way."},{"time":257000,"text":"So here the world is put out of focus,"},{"time":260000,"text":"while our visual dependence is put into focus."},{"time":264000,"text":"The public, you know, once disoriented"},{"time":267000,"text":"can actually ascend to the angel deck above"},{"time":271000,"text":"and then just come down under those lips into the water bar."},{"time":274000,"text":"So, all the waters of the world are served there,"},{"time":276000,"text":"so we thought that, you know, after being at the water"},{"time":280000,"text":"and moving through the water and breathing the water,"},{"time":283000,"text":"you could also drink this building."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286000,"text":"And so it is sort of a theme,"},{"time":290000,"text":"but it goes a little bit, you know, deeper than that."},{"time":293000,"text":"We really wanted to bring out"},{"time":295000,"text":"our absolute dependence on this master sense,"},{"time":299000,"text":"and maybe share our kind of sensibility with our other senses."},{"time":303000,"text":"You know, when we did this project it was a kind of tough sell,"},{"time":307000,"text":"because the Swiss said, \"Well, why are we going to spend, you know,"},{"time":309000,"text":"10 million dollars producing an effect"},{"time":313000,"text":"that we already have in natural abundance that we hate?\""},{"time":315000,"text":"And, you know, we thought -- well, we tried to convince them."},{"time":320000,"text":"And in the end, you know, they adapted this as a national icon"},{"time":326000,"text":"that came to represent Swiss doubt, which we -- you know,"},{"time":331000,"text":"it was kind of a meaning machine"},{"time":333000,"text":"that everybody kind of laid on their own meanings off of."},{"time":335000,"text":"Anyway, it's a temporary structure that was ultimately destroyed,"},{"time":338000,"text":"and so it's now a memory of an apparition, actually,"},{"time":342000,"text":"but it continues to live in edible form."},{"time":345000,"text":"And this is the highest honor"},{"time":347000,"text":"to be bestowed upon an architect in Switzerland -- to have a chocolate bar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352000,"text":"Anyway, moving along."},{"time":354000,"text":"So in the '80s and '90s, we were mostly known for independent work,"},{"time":359000,"text":"such as installation artist, architect,"},{"time":363000,"text":"commissioned projects by museums and non-for-profit organizations."},{"time":368000,"text":"And we did a lot of media work,"},{"time":371000,"text":"also a lot of experimental theater projects."},{"time":373000,"text":"In 2003, the Whitney mounted a retrospective of our work"},{"time":378000,"text":"that featured a lot of this work from the '80s and '90s."},{"time":382000,"text":"However, the work itself resisted the very nature of a retrospective,"},{"time":388000,"text":"and this is just some of the stuff that was in the show."},{"time":391000,"text":"This was a piece on tourism in the United States."},{"time":394000,"text":"This is \"Soft Sell\" for 42nd Street."},{"time":397000,"text":"This was something done at the Cartier Foundation."},{"time":400000,"text":"\"Master/Slave\" at the MOMA, the project series, a piece called \"Parasite.\""},{"time":405000,"text":"And so there were many, many of these kinds of projects."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408000,"text":"Anyway, they gave us the whole fourth floor, and, you know,"},{"time":414000,"text":"the problem of the retrospective"},{"time":416000,"text":"was something we were very uncomfortable with."},{"time":418000,"text":"It's a kind of invention of the museum"},{"time":420000,"text":"that's supposed to bring a kind of cohesive understanding"},{"time":424000,"text":"to the public of a body of work."},{"time":426000,"text":"And our work doesn't really resolve itself into a body in any way at all."},{"time":431000,"text":"And one of the recurring themes, by the way, that in the work"},{"time":436000,"text":"was a kind of hostility toward the museum itself,"},{"time":439000,"text":"and asking about the conventions of the museum, like the wall, the white wall."},{"time":444000,"text":"So, what you see here"},{"time":446000,"text":"is basically a plan of many installations that were put there."},{"time":449000,"text":"And we actually had to install white walls"},{"time":452000,"text":"to separate these pieces, which didn't belong together."},{"time":454000,"text":"But these white walls became a kind of target and weapon at the same time."},{"time":459000,"text":"We used the wall to partition the 13 installations of the project"},{"time":462000,"text":"and produce a kind of acoustic and visual separation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467000,"text":"And what you see is -- actually,"},{"time":469000,"text":"the red dotted line shows the track of this performing element,"},{"time":474000,"text":"which was a new piece that created -- that we created for the --"},{"time":477000,"text":"which was a robotic drill, basically, that went all the way around,"},{"time":481000,"text":"cruised the museum, went all around the walls and did a lot of damage."},{"time":487000,"text":"So, the drill was mounted on this robotic arm."},{"time":490000,"text":"We worked with, by the way, Honeybee Robotics. This is the brain."},{"time":494000,"text":"Honeybee Robotics designed the Mars Driller,"},{"time":497000,"text":"and it was really very much fun to work with them."},{"time":499000,"text":"They weren't doing their primary work, which was for the government,"},{"time":503000,"text":"while they were helping us with this."},{"time":506000,"text":"In any case, the way it works is that"},{"time":508000,"text":"an intelligent navigator basically maps the entire surface of these walls."},{"time":514000,"text":"So, unfolded it's about 300 linear feet."},{"time":517000,"text":"And it randomly generates points within a three-dimensional matrix."},{"time":521000,"text":"It selects a point, it guides the drill to that point, it pierces the dry wall,"},{"time":526000,"text":"leaving a half-inch hole before traveling to the next location."},{"time":531000,"text":"Initially these holes were lone blemishes,"},{"time":535000,"text":"and as the exhibition continued"},{"time":537000,"text":"the walls became increasingly perforated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540000,"text":"So eventually holes on both sides of the wall aligned,"},{"time":543000,"text":"opening views from gallery to gallery."},{"time":545000,"text":"Clusters of holes randomly opened up sections of wall."},{"time":549000,"text":"And so this was a three-month performance piece"},{"time":552000,"text":"in which the wall was made into kind of an increasingly unstable element."},{"time":559000,"text":"And also the acoustic separation was destroyed."},{"time":563000,"text":"Also the visual separation."},{"time":565000,"text":"And there was also this constant background groan, which was very annoying."},{"time":571000,"text":"And this is one of the blackout spaces"},{"time":573000,"text":"where there's a video piece that became totally not useful."},{"time":576000,"text":"So rather than securing a neutral background for the artworks on display,"},{"time":580000,"text":"the wall now actively competed for attention."},{"time":584000,"text":"And this acoustical nuisance and visual nuisance"},{"time":588000,"text":"basically exposed the discomfort of the work"},{"time":591000,"text":"to this encompassing nature of the retrospective."},{"time":597000,"text":"It was really great when it started to break up all of the curatorial text."}]},{"cues":[{"time":601000,"text":"Moving along to a project that we finished about a year ago."},{"time":605000,"text":"It's the ICA -- the Institute of Contemporary Art -- in Boston,"},{"time":610000,"text":"which is on the waterfront."},{"time":612000,"text":"And there's not enough time to really introduce the building,"},{"time":615000,"text":"but I'll simply say that the building negotiates"},{"time":617000,"text":"between this outwardly focused nature of the site --"},{"time":623000,"text":"you know, it's a really great waterfront site in Boston --"},{"time":626000,"text":"and this contradictory other desire to have an inwardly focused museum."},{"time":631000,"text":"So, the nature of the building is that it looks at looking --"},{"time":635000,"text":"I mean that's its primary objective,"},{"time":638000,"text":"both its program and its architectural conceit."},{"time":644000,"text":"The building incorporates the site,"},{"time":648000,"text":"but it dispenses it in very small doses"},{"time":652000,"text":"in the way that the museum is choreographed."},{"time":655000,"text":"So, you come in and you're basically squeezed by the theater,"},{"time":659000,"text":"by the belly of the theater, into this very compressed space"},{"time":661000,"text":"where the view is turned off."},{"time":663000,"text":"Then you come up in this glass elevator right near the curtain wall."},{"time":668000,"text":"This elevator's about the size of a New York City studio apartment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":672000,"text":"And then, this is a view going up,"},{"time":674000,"text":"and then you could come into the theater,"},{"time":676000,"text":"which can actually deny the view or open it up and become a backdrop."},{"time":681000,"text":"And many musicians choose to use the theater glass walls totally open."},{"time":687000,"text":"The view is denied in the galleries"},{"time":689000,"text":"where we receive just natural light,"},{"time":692000,"text":"and then exposed again in the north gallery with a panoramic view."},{"time":697000,"text":"The original intention of this space,"},{"time":699000,"text":"which was unfortunately never realized,"},{"time":702000,"text":"was to use lenticular glass"},{"time":704000,"text":"which allowed only a kind of perpendicular view out."},{"time":707000,"text":"In this very narrow space that connects east and west galleries"},{"time":710000,"text":"the intention was really to not get a climax,"},{"time":714000,"text":"but to have the view stalk you,"},{"time":716000,"text":"so the view would open up as you walked from one end to the other."},{"time":720000,"text":"This was eliminated because the view was too good,"},{"time":723000,"text":"and the mayor said, \"No, we just want this open.\""},{"time":726000,"text":"The architect lost here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":728000,"text":"But culminating -- and that's where this hooks into the theme of my little talk --"},{"time":731000,"text":"is this Mediatheque,"},{"time":733000,"text":"which is suspended from the cantilevered portion of the building."},{"time":737000,"text":"So this is an 80-foot cantilever -- it's quite substantial."},{"time":740000,"text":"So, it's already sticking out into space enough,"},{"time":744000,"text":"and then from that is this, is this small area called the Mediatheque."},{"time":749000,"text":"The Mediatheque has something like 16 stations"},{"time":753000,"text":"where the public can get onto the server"},{"time":755000,"text":"and look at digital artworks or also curated artworks off the web."},{"time":759000,"text":"And this was really a kind of very important part of this building,"},{"time":766000,"text":"and here is a point where architecture --"},{"time":768000,"text":"this is like technology-free -- architecture is only a framing device,"},{"time":772000,"text":"it only edits the harbor view, the industrial harbor"},{"time":776000,"text":"just through its walls, its floors and its ceiling,"},{"time":780000,"text":"to only expose the water itself, the texture of water,"},{"time":786000,"text":"much like a hypnotic effect created by electronic snow"},{"time":790000,"text":"or a lava lamp or something like that."},{"time":793000,"text":"And here is where we really felt that there was a great convergence"},{"time":797000,"text":"of the technological and the natural in the project."},{"time":802000,"text":"But there is just no information, it's just -- it's just hypnosis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":809000,"text":"Moving along to Lincoln Center."},{"time":812000,"text":"These are the guys that did the project in the first place, 50 years ago."},{"time":816000,"text":"We're taking over now, doing work that ranges in scale"},{"time":819000,"text":"from small-scale repairs to major renovations and major facility expansions."},{"time":825000,"text":"But we're doing it with a lot less testosterone."},{"time":828000,"text":"This is the extent of the work that's to be completed by 2010."},{"time":833000,"text":"And for the purposes of this talk,"},{"time":835000,"text":"I wanted to isolate just a part of a project that's even a part of a project"},{"time":839000,"text":"that touches a little bit on this theme of architectural special effects,"},{"time":843000,"text":"and it happens to be our current obsession,"},{"time":847000,"text":"and it plays a little bit with the purging and adding of distraction."},{"time":853000,"text":"It's Alice Tully Hall, and it's tucked under the Juilliard Building"},{"time":857000,"text":"and descends several levels under the street."},{"time":861000,"text":"So, this is the entrance to Tully Hall as it used to be,"},{"time":865000,"text":"before the renovation, which we just started."},{"time":867000,"text":"And we asked ourselves, why couldn't it be exhibitionistic,"},{"time":870000,"text":"like the Met, or like some of the other buildings at Lincoln Center?"},{"time":873000,"text":"And one of the things that we were asked to do"},{"time":876000,"text":"was give it a street identity, expand the lobbies and make it visually accessible."},{"time":881000,"text":"And this building, which is just naturally hermetic, we stripped."},{"time":885000,"text":"We basically did a striptease, architectural striptease,"},{"time":888000,"text":"where we're framing with this kind of canopy --"},{"time":893000,"text":"the underside of three levels of expansion of Juilliard,"},{"time":896000,"text":"about 45,000 square feet -- cutting it to the angle of Broadway,"},{"time":901000,"text":"and then exposing, using that canopy to frame Tully Hall."},{"time":906000,"text":"Before and after shot. (Applause)"},{"time":910000,"text":"Wait a minute, it's just in that state, we have a long way to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":914000,"text":"But what I wanted to do was take a couple of seconds that I have left"},{"time":917000,"text":"to just talk about the hall itself,"},{"time":919000,"text":"which is kind of where we're really doing a massive amount of work."},{"time":923000,"text":"So, the hall is a multi-purpose hall."},{"time":926000,"text":"The clients have asked us to produce a great chamber music hall."},{"time":931000,"text":"Now, that's really tough to do with a hall that has 1,100 seats."},{"time":935000,"text":"Chamber and the notion of chamber has to do with salons"},{"time":938000,"text":"and small-scale performances. They asked us to bring an intimacy."},{"time":941000,"text":"How do you bring an intimacy into a hall?"},{"time":944000,"text":"Intimacy for us means a lot of different things."},{"time":946000,"text":"It means acoustic intimacy and it means visual intimacy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":950000,"text":"One thing is that the subway is running and rumbling right under the hall."},{"time":954000,"text":"Another thing that could be fixed is the shape of the hall."},{"time":956000,"text":"It's like a coffin, it basically sends all the sound,"},{"time":959000,"text":"like a gutter-ball effect, down the aisles."},{"time":961000,"text":"The walls are made of absorptive surface,"},{"time":964000,"text":"half absorptive, half reflective,"},{"time":966000,"text":"which is not very good for concert sound."}]},{"cues":[{"time":969000,"text":"This is Avery Fisher Hall, but the notion of junk -- visual junk --"},{"time":973000,"text":"was very, very important to us, to get rid of visual noise."},{"time":977000,"text":"Because we can't eliminate a single seat,"},{"time":979000,"text":"the architecture is restricted to 18 inches."},{"time":982000,"text":"So it's a very, very thin architecture."},{"time":985000,"text":"First we do a kind of partial box and box separation,"},{"time":989000,"text":"to take away the distraction of the subway noise."},{"time":991000,"text":"Next we wrap the entire hall -- almost like this Olivetti keyboard --"},{"time":996000,"text":"with a material, with a wood material"},{"time":999000,"text":"that basically covers all the surfaces:"},{"time":1001000,"text":"wall, ceiling, floor, stage, steps, everything, boxes."},{"time":1005000,"text":"But it's acoustically engineered to focus the sound into the house"},{"time":1009000,"text":"and back to the stage. And here's an acoustic shelf."},{"time":1012000,"text":"Looking up the hall. Just a section of the stage."},{"time":1015000,"text":"Just everything is lined, it incorporates --"},{"time":1018000,"text":"every single thing that you could possibly imagine"},{"time":1020000,"text":"is tucked into this high-performance skin."},{"time":1022000,"text":"But one more added feature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1024000,"text":"So now that we've stripped the hall of all visual distraction,"},{"time":1027000,"text":"everything that prevents this intimacy"},{"time":1030000,"text":"which is supposed to connect the house, the audience,"},{"time":1033000,"text":"with the performers, we add one little detail,"},{"time":1037000,"text":"one piece of architectural excess, a special effect: lighting."},{"time":1041000,"text":"We very strongly believe that the theatrics of a concert hall"},{"time":1045000,"text":"is as much in the space of intermission and the space of arrival"},{"time":1049000,"text":"as it is when the concert starts."},{"time":1051000,"text":"So what we wanted to do was produce this effect,"},{"time":1055000,"text":"this lighting effect,"},{"time":1057000,"text":"which made us have to bioengineer the wood walls."},{"time":1061000,"text":"And what it entails is the use of resin, of this very thick resin"},{"time":1067000,"text":"with a veneer of the same kind of wood that's used throughout the hall,"},{"time":1071000,"text":"in a kind of seamless continuity"},{"time":1075000,"text":"that wraps the hall in light, like a belt of light: rather than separating,"},{"time":1080000,"text":"like a proscenium would separate the audience from performers,"},{"time":1084000,"text":"it connects audience with players."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1086000,"text":"And this is a mockup that is in Salt Lake City"},{"time":1092000,"text":"that gives you a sense of what this is going to look like in full-scale."},{"time":1097000,"text":"And this is a guy from Salt Lake City,"},{"time":1100000,"text":"this is what they look like out there."},{"time":1102000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1105000,"text":"And for us, I mean it's really kind of a very strange thing,"},{"time":1108000,"text":"but the moments in the hall that the buzz kind of dies down"},{"time":1114000,"text":"when the audience is waiting for the performance to begin,"},{"time":1117000,"text":"very similar to the parting of curtains or the raising of a chandelier,"},{"time":1121000,"text":"the walls will just exude this glow, temporarily stealing attention from the stage."},{"time":1127000,"text":"And this is Tully in construction now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1131000,"text":"I have no ending to say, except that I'm a couple of minutes over."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1135000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":1137000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}